Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• From the balance sheet, Total Assets = 14,930,535.06 and Total Liabilities are given by the Total Current Liabilities (since there are no non-current liabilities shown), which is 967,271.87.  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 967,271.87 / 14,930,535.06 ≈ 0.0648, which rounds to 0.06.

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio.  
• From the cash flow statement, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 116,257.19.  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 963,263.19.  
• Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = 116,257.19 / 963,263.19 ≈ 0.1207, which rounds to 0.12.

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.06",
    "Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio": "0.12"
  }
}
